==English==
===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''vertex'', top, peak, from ''[[vertere]]'', to turn

===Noun===
'''vertex''' (''plural'' '''vertices''')

#The highest point of something.
#{{geometry}} A corner of a [[polygon]] (where two [[side]]s meet) or of a [[polyhedron]] (where three or more [[face]]s and an equal number of [[edge]]s meet).
#{{alggeom}} The point of intersection of an [[axis]] and a [[curve]].
#(''computer graphics''') A point in 3D space, usually given in terms of its ''x''-, ''y''-, and ''z''-[[coordinate]]s.

